                  <summary>Letter of Lysimachos to Leontiskos and associates, ordering them to pay to Krates the amount still owing on the rent of the orchard of Eirene</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">7 lines written across the fibers; on the back, along the fibers, there are address and docket</note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is calligraphic and chancery</note>
                     <note type="general">The docket, in a smaller hand, was written by the same clerk who wrote the docket of P.Col. IV 121</note>
                     <note type="general">At the end of the letter there is an ornate paragraphos</note>
                     <note type="general">Beautiful seal representing a male head, perhaps Lysimachos himself</note>
                     <note type="general">The words or word-groups are often separated by spaces</note>
